{{short description|Togolese footballer}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Claude Koutob | image = | fullname = Claude Koutob Naoto | height = 1.78 m | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1995|12|26|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Togo]] | currentclub = [[Stade Poitevin FC|Stade Poitevin]] | clubnumber = | position = [[Winger (association football)|Winger]], [[Forward (association football)#Second striker|forward]] | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = 2013–2014 | clubs1 = [[Gbikinti FC de Bassar|Gbikinti]] | caps1 = | goals1 = | years2 = 2014–2015 | clubs2 = [[AS Marsa]] | caps2 = 2 | goals2 = 0 | years3 = 2015–2017 | clubs3 = [[Vendée Poiré-sur-Vie Football|Poiré-sur-Vie]] | caps3 = 16 | goals3 = 7 | years4 = 2017–2019 | clubs4 = [[Les Herbiers VF|Les Herbiers B]] | caps4 = 26 | goals4 = 13 | years5 = 2017–2019 | clubs5 = [[Les Herbiers VF|Les Herbiers]] | caps5 = 28 | goals5 = 2 | years6 = 2019– | clubs6 = [[Stade Poitevin FC|Stade Poitevin]] | caps6 = 7 | goals6 = 1 | club-update = 15:53, 18 November 2019 (UTC) }}
'''Claude Koutob Naoto''' (born December 26, 1995) is a [[Togo]]lese [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Winger (association football)|winger]] or [[Forward (association football)#Second striker|forward]] for [[Stade Poitevin FC]].
==Club career== Koutob Naoto started his career in Togo with [[Gbikinti FC de Bassar|Gbikinti]] before moving to Tunisian side [[AS Marsa]] in 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.africatopsports.com/2014/08/25/claude-koutob-togolais-rejoint-las-marsa/|title=Claude Koutob: Le Togolais Rejoint L'as Marsa|last=Lavon|first=Steve|date=25 August 2014|website=www.africatopsports.com|language=fr|accessdate=16 March 2016}}</ref>
After making two professional appearances in the [[Tunisian Ligue Professionnelle 1]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.africatopsports.com/2014/10/20/claude-koutob-togolais-prend-ses-marques-en-tunisie/|title=Claude Koutob: Le Togolais Prend Ses Marques En Tunisie|last=Lavon|first=Steve|date=20 October 2014|website=www.africatopsports.com/|language=fr|accessdate=16 March 2016}}</ref> Koutob Naoto left Marsa for French outfit [[Vendée Poiré-sur-Vie Football|Poiré-sur-Vie]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.africatopsports.com/2015/12/11/charles-acolatse-lautre-togolais-du-poiree-sur-vie/|title=Charles Acolaste: L’autre Togolais Du Poirée Sur Vie|last=Lavon|first=Steve|date=11 December 2015|website=www.africatopsports.com|language=fr|accessdate=16 March 2016}}</ref> ciao
==International career== Koutob Naoto was called up to the [[Togo national football team]] for a [[2014 FIFA World Cup qualification (CAF)|2014 World Cup qualification]] game against the [[DR Congo national football team|DR Congo]] on 8 September 2013. However, he never came off the bench.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.com/gamecast/statistics/id/334458/statistics.html|title=Togo 2-1 DR Congo|date=8 September 2013|website=www.espnfc.com|publisher=ESPN|accessdate=16 March 2016}}</ref>
