{{short description|Libyan footballer}} {{Infobox football biography |name= Ali Musrati |fullname = Almoatasembellah Ali Mohamed Musrati |image = |birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1996|4|6|df=yes}} |birth_place = [[Misrata]], Libya |height = {{height|m=1.86}} |currentclub = [[S.C. Braga|Braga]] |clubnumber = |position = [[Midfielder]] |years1 = 2013–2017 |clubs1 = [[Al-Ittihad Club (Tripoli)|Al-Ittihad Tripoli]] |caps1 = |goals1 = |years2 = 2017–2019 |clubs2 = [[Vitória S.C. B|Vitória Guimarães B]] |caps2 = 40 |goals2 = 1 |years3 = 2019–2020 |clubs3 = [[Vitória S.C.|Vitória Guimarães]] |caps3 = 5 |goals3 = 0 |years4 = 2020 |clubs4 = → [[Rio Ave F.C.|Rio Ave]] (loan) |caps4 = 12 |goals4 = 0 |years5 = 2020– |clubs5 = [[S.C. Braga|Braga]] |caps5 = 0 |goals5 = 0 |nationalyears1 = 2014– |nationalteam1 = [[Libya national football team|Libya]] |nationalcaps1 = 35 |nationalgoals1 = 2 |club-update = 22 February 2020 |nationalteam-update = 19 November 2019 }} '''Almoatasembellah Ali Mohamed Musrati''', known as '''Ali Musrati''' or '''Ali Al Musrati''' ({{lang-ar|المعتصم بالله علي محمد المصراتي}}; born 6 April 1996) is a Libyan [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for Portuguese club [[S.C. Braga]].
==Club career== Born in [[Misrata]], Elmusrati began his career at [[Al-Ittihad Club (Tripoli)]]. In January 2017 he signed a three-and-a-half-year deal at [[Vitória S.C.]] of Portugal's [[Primeira Liga]], on the recommendation of their former player [[Romano Sion]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Andrade |first1=Tomaz |title="Al Musrati tem grande futuro, daqui a dois anos não está cá"|trans-title="Al Musrati has a big future, two years from now he won't be here" |url=https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/1a-liga/vitoria-guimaraes/noticias/li-5681099.html |accessdate=27 February 2020 |work=[[O Jogo]] |date=21 February 2017 |language=Portuguese}}</ref> He began playing for their [[Vitória S.C. B|reserve team]] in [[LigaPro]], and on 4 March 2018 scored his first goal to equalise in a 1–1 draw away to [[C.F. União]].<ref>{{cite news |title=U. Madeira-V. Guimarães B, 1-1: Madeirenses não seguraram a vantagem|trans-title=U. Madeira-V. Guimarães B, 1-1: Madeirans fail to keep the lead|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/2--liga/detalhe/u-madeira-v-guimaraes-b-1-1-madeirenses-nao-seguraram-a-vantagem |accessdate=27 February 2020 |work=[[Record (newspaper)|Record]] |date=4 March 2018 |language=Portuguese}}</ref>
On 5 August 2019, Elmusrati made his debut for the first team of the club from [[Guimarães]], playing the full 90 minutes of a 1–0 win at [[C.D. Feirense]] in the second round of the [[Taça da Liga]].<ref>{{cite news |title=V. Guimarães elimina Feirense e está na fase de grupos da Taça da Liga|trans-title=V. Guimarães eliminate Feirense and are in the group phase of the Taça da Liga |url=https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/taca-liga/noticias/v-guimaraes-elimina-feirense-e-esta-na-fase-de-grupos-da-taca-da-liga-11183846.html |accessdate=27 February 2020 |work=O Jogo |date=5 August 2019 |language=Portuguese}}</ref> Thirteen days later he made his [[Primeira Liga]] debut in a 1–1 home draw with [[Boavista F.C.]] and was third-place in the vote for the league's best midfielder of the month, behind [[Bruno Fernandes (footballer, born 1994)|Bruno Fernandes]] and [[Pizzi (Portuguese footballer)|Pizzi]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Bruno Fernandes eleito o melhor médio do mês de agosto|trans-title=Bruno Fernandes chosen as best midfielder in the month of August |url=https://bancada.pt/futebol/portugal/bruno-fernandes-eleito-o-melhor-medio-do-mes-de-agosto |accessdate=27 February 2020 |publisher=Bancada |date=11 September 2019 |language=Portuguese}}</ref>
Elmusrati was loaned to [[Rio Ave F.C.]] of the same league on 29 January 2020, for the rest of the season.<ref>{{cite news |title=Rio Ave garante empréstimo de Al Musrati |trans-title=Rio Ave secure loan of Al Musrati|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/rio-ave/detalhe/rio-ave-garante-emprestimo-de-al-musrati |accessdate=27 February 2020 |work=Record |date=29 January 2020 |language=Portuguese}}</ref> He, [[Diogo Figueiras]] and [[Nuno Santos (footballer, born 1995)|Nuno Santos]] were sent off on 17 June in a 2–1 home loss to [[S.L. Benfica]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Benfica vence em Vila do Conde perante Rio Ave que terminou com nove|trans-title=Benfica win in Vila do Conde against a Rio Ave who finished with nine |url=https://guardiao-ao.com/2020/06/18/benfica-vence-em-vila-do-conde-perante-rio-ave-que-terminou-com-nove/ |accessdate=1 August 2020 |work=O Guardião |date=18 June 2020 |language=Portuguese}}</ref>
On 31 July 2020, Elmusrati signed a four-year deal at [[S.C. Braga]], joining his former Rio Ave manager [[Carlos Carvalhal]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Al Musrati assina por quatro épocas pelo SC Braga|trans-title=Elmusrati signs for four seasons for SC Braga |url=https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/primeira-liga/artigos/al-musrati-assina-por-quatro-epocas-pelo-sc-braga |accessdate=3 August 2020 |publisher=SAPO |date=31 July 2020 |language=Portuguese}}</ref>
==International career== Elmusrati was first called up for [[Libya national football team|Libya]] at the [[2014 African Nations Championship]] in South Africa, and played all but one game including the penalty shootout win over [[Ghana national football team|Ghana]] in the final.<ref>{{cite news |title=Halftime: Libya 0-0 Ghana |url=https://www.soccerladuma.co.za/news/articles/categories/south-africa/halftime-libya-0-0-ghana/143024?page=1 |accessdate=27 February 2020 |publisher=Soccer Laduma |date=1 February 2014}}</ref><ref name=libya>{{cite news |last1=Alie |first1=Mohammed |title=CHAN 2014: Libya beat Ghana to snatch first African title |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/25719387 |accessdate=27 February 2020 |publisher=[[BBC Sport]] |date=1 February 2014}}</ref> ciao
